<h1>Friedel-Crafts Alkylation</h1>
<p><img src="friede2.gif" width="295" height="61"></p>
<p>This Lewis acid-catalyzed electrophilic aromatic substitution allows the 
synthesis of alkylated products via the reaction of arenes with alkyl 
halides or alkenes. Since alkyl substituents activate the arene 
substrate, polyalkylation may occur. A valuable, two-step alternative is 
Friedel-Crafts Acylation followed by a carbonyl reduction.</p>
<hr>
